  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Life-Saving Multi-Sectoral Assistance to Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) and Other Conflict-Affected Communities in Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Yemen is facing the world&#x2019;s worst humanitarian crisis. Nearly two thirds of the total population (20.7 million people) requires some form of humanitarian and protection assistance, and an estimated 4 million people have been internally displaced since the onset of the conflict. Humanitarian needs are widespread in relation to shelter and non-food items, camp coordination and camp management, and water, sanitation, and hygiene sectors, and cash-based interventions are greatly needed. IOM is committed to ensuring that multi-sectoral assistance is available to the most vulnerable people in Yemen and that internally displaced persons (IDPs), host communities, and migrants are able to live with dignity and access to assistance that meets their most critical needs. IOM is contributing to the improvement of the living conditions and protection of IDPs and conflict affected communities in Yemen, particularly at a time when COVID-19 has eroded coping mechanisms, increased dependency on aid and reduced access to services. Proposed multi-sector humanitarian activities are contextualized to needs, integrating and mainstreaming COVID-19 response outcomes across all programmes.</narrative>
  </description>
